3 album by various artists |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Other appearance \u2013 Music Inspired by The Chronicles of Narnia\">\n{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000AXWH26 |title=Music Inspired by The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe \u2013 album by various artists |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Other appearance \u2013 Sing Over Me\">\n{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000GEU6FO |title=Sing Over Me: Worship Songs & Lullabies \u2013 album by various artists |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Other appearance \u2013 Amazing Grace\">\n{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000LW7UUK |title=Amazing Grace: Music Inspired by the Motion Picture \u2013 album by various artists |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Music video \u2013 Legacy\">\n{{cite AV media |url=http://www.newreleasetuesday.com/videodetail.php?video_id=2340 |people=[[Nichole Nordeman|Nordeman, Nichole]] | date=2002 | title=Legacy | medium=music video |work==New Release Tuesday | publisher=NRT Media Inc}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Music video \u2013 Finally Free\">\n{{cite AV media |url=http://www.godtube.com/watch/?v=JB0F2FNU |people=Nordeman, Nichole | date=2008 | title=Finally Free | medium=music video |work=[[Godtube]] | publisher=[[Salem Web Network]]}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Music video \u2013 Beautiful for Me\">\n{{cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=orc4TuIO56s |people=Nordeman, Nichole | date=2010 | title=Beautiful for Me | medium=music video |work=[[YouTube]] | publisher=YouTube, LLC }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"CBN \u2013 Recollection\">\n{{cite web |url=https://www.cbn.com/cbnmusic/interviews/jej_NicholeNordeman050507.aspx |title=Nichole Nordeman's Legacy |first=Jennifer |last=Jones |publisher=[[Christian Broadcasting Network]] |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Beliefnet \u2013 The Story\">\n{{cite web |url=http://www.beliefnet.com/columnists/wholenotes/2011/10/nichole-nordeman-talks-about-life-away-from.html |title=Dove Award winning singer/songwriter Nichole Nordeman talks about life away from full-time music and writing songs for \"The Story\" |first=Chad |last=Bonham |work=[[Beliefnet]] |publisher=BN Media Associates |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Nichole Nordeman Instagram\">\n{{cite web |url=http://instagram.com/p/kkEErJLH-H/ |title=Nichole Nordeman: I'm writing for a new record  |publisher=[[Instagram]] |accessdate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Amazon Bio \u2013 Nichole Nordeman\">\n{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/-/e/B008XLHXT4 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6O6dFsbtl?url=http://www.amazon.com/Nichole-Nordeman/e/B008XLHXT4 |title=About Nichole Nordeman |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=March 16, 2014 |archivedate=March 16, 2014  }}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"Hits Daily Double\">\n{{cite web |url=http://hitsdailydouble.com/new_album_releases |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150829191011/http://hitsdailydouble.com/new_album_releases |title=Upcoming Releases |publisher=Hits Digital Ventures |accessdate=August 29, 2015 |archivedate=August 29, 2015 }}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=mn0000396144|tab=discography|label=Nichole Nordeman discography}}\n\n{{Nichole Nordeman}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nordeman, Nichole}}\n[[Category:Discographies of American artists]]\n[[Category:Christian music discographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = [[Nichole Nordeman]]\n| Image        = \n| Caption      = \n| Alt          = \n| Studio       = 5\n| Live         = 1\n| Compilation  = 4\n| Video        = \n| Music videos = 3\n| EP           = 1\n| Singles      = 18\n| B-sides      = \n| Soundtrack   = 1\n}}\n\nAmerican singer-songwriter [[Nichole Nordeman]] has released five [[studio album]]s, one [[live album]], four [[compilation album]]s, one [[extended play]], one [[soundtrack album]], eighteen [[Single (music)|single]]s, and three [[music video]]s. In 1998, after winning a contest sponsored by the [[Gospel Music Association]], Nordeman was signed to [[Star Song Communications]] and [[Sparrow Records]] and began to work on her debut studio album, ''[[Wide Eyed (Nichole Nordeman album)|Wide Eyed]]''.<ref name=\"Allmusic \u2013 Biography\" /> The album was released on September 1998 and entered the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Christian Albums]] and ''Billboard'' [[Top Heatseekers|Heatseekers Albums]] charts at number 16 and 29, respectively, both of which marked her chart debut. ''Wide Eyed'' spawned four singles, \"To Know You,\" \"Who You Are,\" \"I Wish the Same\", and \"Wide Eyed\", and has sold 130,000 copies in the United States.<ref name=\"Allmusic \u2013 Biography\" /> In May  2000, Nordeman released her second studio album, ''[[This Mystery]]'', which charted on the ''Billboard'' Christian Albums chart at 12.<ref name=\"Albums \u2013 Allmusic\" /> Three singles, \"This Mystery,\" \"Fool For You\" and \"Every Season\", were released from ''This Mystery''.<ref name=\"Single release \u2013 Tremble\" /><ref name=\"Single release \u2013 Every Season\" /> Nordeman's third studio album, ''[[Woven & Spun]]'', was released on September 2002. The album entered the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart at number 136 and at the ''Billboard'' Christian Albums chart at number five. All three of ''Woven & Spun''{{'}}s singles, \"Holy\", \"Legacy\", and \"Even Then\", became [[Top 40|top forty]] hits on the ''Billboard'' [[Christian Songs]] chart. \"Holy\" spent 10 weeks at number one on the Christian AC radio charts. In May 2003, Nordeman released her first [[live album]], ''Live at the Door'', which was recorded at [[Deep Ellum, Dallas|The Door]] music venue in Dallas, Texas. In May 2005, she released her fourth studio album, ''[[Brave (Nichole Nordeman album)|Brave]]''. The album entered the ''Billboard'' 200 chart at number 119 and at the ''Billboard'' Christian Albums chart at number two, marking Nordeman's career highest charting debut. Its lead single and title track became her first [[List of number-one Billboard Christian Songs of the 2000s|''Billboard'' number one hit]] on the ''Billboard'' Christian Songs chart, while its two succeeding singles, \"What If\" and \"Real to Me\", became top twenty hits on the chart.\n\nIn 2007, Nordeman released her first [[greatest hits album]], ''[[Recollection: The Best of Nichole Nordeman]]'' before taking hiatus in her music career.<ref name=\"CBN \u2013 Recollection\" /><ref name=\"Beliefnet \u2013 The Story\" /> The album's lead single, \"Sunrise\", charted within the top forty of the ''Billboard'' Christian Songs chart. In 2010, during her hiatus, Nordeman collaborated with Canadian record producer Bernie Herms to write and produce the concept soundtrack album, ''[[Music Inspired by The Story]]'', which was released on September 2011.<ref name=\"Beliefnet \u2013 The Story\" /> The album charted on the ''Billboard'' 200 and the Christian Albums charts at numbers 135 and 11, respectively. Its lead single, \"I'm With You\", a duet with recording artist [[Amy Grant]], charted on the  ''Billboard'' Christian Songs chart at number 29. Between 2010\u20132013, Nordeman has released the singles, \"Beautiful for Me\", \"[[The Heavenly Vision|Turn Your Eyes Upon Jesus (Look Up)]]\", and \"Real\", before announcing intentions to release a record.<ref name=\"Nichole Nordeman Instagram\" /> In 2015, she released her first extended play, ''[[The Unmaking]]''.<ref name=\"EP release \u2013 The Unmaking\" /> According to the [[Capitol Christian Music Group]], Nordeman has sold over one million records.<ref name=\"Amazon Bio \u2013 Nichole Nordeman\" />\n\n== Albums ==\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected ch