 Noble\n   |votes      = 5,247\n   |percentage = 29.42\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link\n   |party      = Social Credit Party (New Zealand)\n   |candidate  = Rodney Wilson\n   |votes      = 4,009\n   |percentage = 22.48\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box majority\n   |votes      = 3,330\n   |percentage = 18.67\n   |change     = +2.69\n }}\n {{Election box turnout\n   |votes      = 17,833\n   |percentage = 86.19\n   |change     = +16.18\n }}\n {{Election box Registered electors\n   |reg. electors = 20,688\n }}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===1978 election===\n{{Election box begin | title=[[1978 New Zealand general election|1978 general election]]: Te Atatu{{sfn|Norton|1988|p=361}}\n}}\n {{Election box winning candidate with party link\n   |party      = New Zealand Labour Party\n   |candidate  = [[Michael Bassett]]\n   |votes      = 8,640\n   |percentage = 48.99\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link\n   |party      = New Zealand National Party\n   |candidate  = W R Cross\n   |votes      = 5,821\n   |percentage = 33.01\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link\n   |party      = Social Credit Party (New Zealand)\n   |candidate  = John Geoffrey Rawson\n   |votes      = 2,923\n   |percentage = 16.57\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link\n   |party      = Values Party\n   |candidate  = D C Bartle\n   |votes      = 250\n   |percentage = 1.41\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box majority\n   |votes      = 2,819\n   |percentage = 15.98\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box turnout\n   |votes      = 17,634\n   |percentage = 70.01\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box Registered electors\n   |reg. electors = 25,186\n }}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite book |ref=harv |title=Electoral Atlas of New Zealand |last=McRobie |first=Alan |year=1989 |publisher=GP Books |location=Wellington |isbn=0-477-01384-8}}\n*{{Cite book |ref=harv |last= Wilson |first= James Oakley |title= New Zealand Parliamentary Record, 1840\u20131984 |edition= 4th |origyear= First ed. published 1913 |year= 1985 |publisher= V.R. Ward, Govt. Printer |location= Wellington |oclc=154283103}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.parliament.nz/NR/rdonlyres/6F3F94F4-8126-474B-BB0B-11FC627C2F11/204/Te_Atatu1.pdf Electorate Profile]  ''Parliamentary Library''\n{{electorates of New Zealand}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Te Atatu (New Zealand electorate)}}\n[[Category:New Zealand electorates]]\n[[Category:Politics of the Auckland Region]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:1996 disestablishments in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:1999 establishments in New Zealand]]\n", "name_user": "Not Another NPC", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2017 election:added + sign", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Te_Atat%C5%AB_(New_Zealand_electorate)"}
{"title_page": "Hyena (soundtrack)", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Hyena\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     =\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 3, 2006\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[K-pop]], [[jazz]], [[blues]]\n| length     =\n| language   = [[Korean language|Korean]]\n| label      = [[SM Entertainment]]\n| producer   = [[Lee Soo-man]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n'''''Hyena''''' is the name of a [[soundtrack]] released in 2006 for the [[Korean drama]] ''Hyena'' (\ud558\uc774\uc5d0\ub098), which aired on [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] and starred [[Kim Min-jong]], [[Yoon Da-hoon]], [[Oh Man-seok]] and [[Shin Sung-rok]].\n\n==Track listing==\n# The Night Chicago Died - [[Super Junior-K.R.Y.]]\n# Go! Go! - [[TRAX (band)|TRAX]]\n# \ud55c \uc0ac\ub78c\ub9cc\uc744 (The One I Love) - [[Super Junior-K.R.Y.]]\n# 0 (\uc601 ; \u96f6) - [[Seo Hyun-jin]]\n# Smile - [[Cho Kyuhyun|Kyuhyun]] ([[Super Junior]])\n# Bossa Cha Cha - Lee Yoon-jae\n# My Tears - [[TRAX (band)|TRAX]]\n# \uadf8\ub300 \ub5a0\ub098\uac00\ub294 \uae38\uc5d0 (You Go Away on the Road) - [[Chu Ga-yeoul]]\n# Drive\n# \ud55c \uc0ac\ub78c\ub9cc\uc744 (The One I Love) (Instrumental) \n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.chtvn.com/ tvN's official website] {{in lang|ko}}\n\n[[Category:Soundtracks by South Korean artists]]\n[[Category:2006 soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Television soundtracks]]\n[[Category:SM Entertainment soundtracks]]\n[[Category:K-pop albums]]\n[[Category:Jazz soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Blues soundtracks]]\n\n\n{{soundtrack-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Hyena\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     =\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 3, 2006\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[K-pop]], [[jazz]], [[blues]]\n| length     =\n| language