erning Territories|territory]] claimed and occupied mostly by Morocco {{nowrap|as its [[Southern Provinces]]}}\n| capital                = [[Rabat]]\n| coordinates                = {{Coord|34|02|N|6|51|W|type:city}}\n| largest_city                = [[Casablanca]]<br>{{small|{{coord|33|32|N|7|35|W|display=inline}}}}\n| official_languages                = {{hlist |[[Modern Standard Arabic|Arabic]]| [[Standard Moroccan Berber|Berber]] }}\n| languages_type                = Spoken languages\n| languages                = {{ublist|class=nowrap |[[Moroccan Arabic|Darija]]|[[Berber languages|Berber]]|[[Hassaniya Arabic|Hassaniya ]]|\n[[French language|French]]<ref group=\"note\" name=\"French\">[[French language|French]] is also used in official government documents and by the business community, although it has no official status: \"French (often the language of business, government, and diplomacy)...\" [https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/mo.html] \u2013 See [[French language in Morocco]] for further information</ref>}}\n| languages2_type                = Foreign languages\n| languages2                =[[English language|English]] \u2022 [[Spanish language|Spanish]]\n| ethnic_groups                = <!--The following is sourced (see ethnic_groups_year above), so please do not change it without also replacing that source:-->{{ublist|[[Arab-Berber]] 99%|Other 1%}}<ref name=CIApop/>\n| ethnic_groups_year                = 2014{{lower|0.2em|<ref name=CIA>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/mo.html |title=Morocco |work=World Factbook |publisher=Central Intelligence Agency}}</ref>}}\n| demonym                = [[Moroccan people|Moroccan]]\n| government_type                = [[Unitary state|Unitary]] [[Parliamentary system|parliamentary]] [[constitutional monarchy]]<ref name=\"Const1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.maroc.ma/NR/rdonlyres/2298ADD6-703C-471E-B924-A5E4F396FEA2/0/Texteint%C3%A9gralduprojetdenouvelle