{"title_page": "Nisith Pramanik", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Nisith Pramanik\n| image               = Nisith Pramanik.jpg\n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1986|1|17|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Dinhata]], [[Cooch Behar district|Cooch Behar]], [[West Bengal]]\n| residence           = \n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| office1             = [[Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha]]\n| constituency1       = [[Cooch Behar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Cooch Behar]]\n| term_start1         = 23 May 2019\n| term_end1           = \n| predecessor1        = [[Parthapratim Roy]]\n| successor1          = \n| nationality         = [[India]]n\n| party               = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| otherparty          = [[All India Trinamool Congress]] <br> (till February 2019)\n| spouse              = Priyanka Pramanik\n| children            = 2\n| website             = \n| footnotes           = \n| date                = \n| year                = \n| source              = http://loksabhaph.nic.in/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=5041&lastls=17\n}}\n'''Nisith Pramanik''' (born 17 January 1986) is an Indian politician. He was elected to the [[Lok Sabha]], lower house of the [[Parliament of India]] from [[Cooch Behar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Cooch Behar]], [[West Bengal]] in the [[2019 Indian general election]] as a member of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]. <ref>{{cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/bjp-fares-well-in-minority-concentration-districts-wins-over-50-seats/articleshow/69556665.cms | title=BJP fares well in 'minority-concentration' districts, wins over 50% seats | publisher=[[The Times of India]] | date=29 May 2019 | accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\nHe was also a member of [[All India Trinamool Congress]] (AITC) before joining the [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] in March 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=TMC leader joins BJP, says only PM Modi can save country |url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/tmc-leader-joins-bjp-says-222500604.html |accessdate=10 September 2019 |work=in.news.yahoo.com |date=1 March 2019 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=ANI |title=TMC leader joins BJP, says only PM Modi can save country |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/tmc-leader-joins-bjp-says-only-pm-modi-can-save-country/videoshow/68215587.cms?from=mdr |accessdate=12 February 2020 |date=1 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[Nisith Pramanik]] was born on the dawn of 17<sup>th</sup> January 1986 to a middle class family of a farmer owning own lands for farming in [[Bhetaguri]], [[Cooch Behar|Coochbehar]] district, [[West Bengal]] state. He was the younger brother of two children born to Bidhu Bhushan Pramanik and Chhanda Pramanik .Nisith's family belonged to the [[Rajbanshi]] community, which is categorised as an [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule caste]] by the Indian government.\n\n== '''Biography''' ==\nAs a child, [[Nisith Pramanik|nisith]] helped his father in various farming works. [[Nisith Pramanik|nisith]] completed his higher secondary education in [[Bhetaguri]]. During his schooling days teacher used to judge [[Nisith Pramanik|nisith]] as an intellectual student who is very good in calculations and having ethical values. But he was well known in school as a good orator.\n\nRight from the childhood he was visionary and always tried to get involved in social activities. Helping others and social mingling inherit quality of Nisith soon made him one or the other ways as younger disciple of god for [[Rajbanshi caste|rajbanshi]] community people. As he steps in youth age unknowingly and without his concern he has become a loving and caring public face among the people due to his helping qualities. He found that his followers are following him blindly and started building lots of expectations from him. Though personally not having any interest in politics but due to his popularity he came in the eyes of various political party leaders. During this time [[West Bengal|Bengal]] was ruled by the communist soon few political leaders tried to drag him towards them while opposition want him to be with them. Here the conflicts started and he became target person for vice versa party. Even during this conflict time he has face life threats and overcome so many life taking attacks on him. This ultimately made him bolder and stronger and he found that at the youth age only he lost the fear of losing life.\n\nHere the turnaround came in his life he took a pledge to dedicate his life for his followers, supporters and to help the needy persons of the society. Soon selfless, honest and dedicated service to the people of the society made him well known in his [[Bhetaguri|local]], nearby areas and in his [[Rajbanshi caste|community.]]\n\nAfter completing his graduation he chose the noble profession of teaching. Having lots of service options and got selected for various services he preferred to serve in Government junior Basic school of [[Burirhat Junior High School|Burirhat]] in his nearby area for the development and to help the deprived people of the society. During his teaching career he started his vision to develop zeal of patriotism amongst the student. His way of teaching soon made him popular among the students and youths of the society. With in short span of teaching career and as a young teacher everybody started calling him lovingly amader [[Elder Brother|\u201cDADA\u201d]] (means Elder Brother) priyo [[Nisith Pramanik|Nisith Da.]]\n\nDuring this time communist rule was going on in West Bengal and [[All India Trinamool Congress|Trinamool]] congress was spreading their Branches in [[north Bengal]] and other parts of [[West Bengal|west Bengal.]] Somewhere or the other due to his popularity people of the society forced him join the politics for various reasons and he got caught in the eyes of Trinamool Congress. Finally as per his characteristics as he likes challenges in life and due to vast support of people he joins [[All India Trinamool Congress|Trinamool Congress]] as a youth leader. Due to his leadership qualities and firm decisive result oriented leader and having mass number of followers, with in very short span of time he became voice of youth [[All India Trinamool Congress|Trinamool congress]] workers of [[Cooch Behar|coochbehar]] district and entire [[North Bengal]] districts.\n\nDuring his presence in [[All India Trinamool Congress|Trinamool congress]] for few years he chaired various prestigious posts and has not left any stone unturned for the betterment of the Party workers, people and his followers.\n\nLater in 2019 by seeing the ideology of [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP party]] and Influenced by the charismatic leadership of Honourable Prime Minister Narendra Modi he made his mind to join Bhartiya Janta party to serve mother India. Like a real fighter he faced all the challenges of opposition and by overcoming all the allegations, barriers and obstacles put by opposition he fought 2019 [[Lok Sabha|loksabha]] elections from [[Cooch Behar|coochbehar]] having only 9 days for campaigning. By the blessings of almighty and huge support of Coochbehar constituency people he won the election by massive margin and became the Member of Parliament.\n\nPat at the back given by Honourable Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi|Shri Narendra Modi]] on the first day he stepped in [[Parliament]] of India inspired him to dedicate his life for [[Bharat Mata|Maa Bharati]] and ultimately these lines came out from his mind,\n\n\n\u201cAlone I am drop of water, Together we are an ocean.\n\nLet\u2019s take a pledge together; we will make Mother India,\n\nOne Nation, Strong Nation\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026.\u201d\n\n== Link's ==\n\n# https://www.ndtv.com/elections/lok-sabha-election-candidates-list-2019/nisith-pramanik-25001-3\n# https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/bjps-nisith-pramanik-arrives-in-parliament-wearing-feathered-turban20190617183158\n\n\n\n<br />\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n*[http://loksabhaph.nic.in/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=5041&lastls=17 Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n\n{{17th Lok Sabha members from all states}}\n{{Bharatiya Janata Party}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pramanik, Nisith}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:17th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from West Bengal]]\n[[Category:People from Cooch Behar]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Nisith Pramanik\n| image               = Nisith Pramanik.jpg\n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1986|1|17|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Dinhata]], [[Cooch Behar district|Cooch Behar]], [[West Bengal]]\n| residence           = \n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| office1             = [[Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha]]\n| constituency1       = [[Cooch Behar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Cooch Behar]]\n| term_start1         = 23 May 2019\n| term_end1           = \n| predecessor1        = [[Parthapratim Roy]]\n| successor1          = \n| nationality         = [[India]]n\n| party               = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| otherparty          = [[All India Trinamool Congress]] <br> (till February 2019)\n| spouse              = Priyanka Pramanik\n| children            = 2\n| website             = \n| footnotes           = \n| date                = \n| year                = \n| source              = http://loksabhaph.nic.in/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=5041&lastls=17\n}}\n'''Nisith Pramanik''' (born 17 January 1986) is an Indian politician. He was elected to the [[Lok Sabha]], lower house of the [[Parliament of India]] from [[Cooch Behar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Cooch Behar]], [[West Bengal]] in the [[2019 Indian general election]] as a member of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]. <ref>{{cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/bjp-fares-well-in-minority-concentration-districts-wins-over-50-seats/articleshow/69556665.cms | title=BJP fares well in 'minority-concentration' districts, wins over 50% seats | publisher=[[The Times of India]] | date=29 May 2019 | accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\nHe was also a member of [[All India Trinamool Congress]] (AITC) before joining the [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] in March 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=TMC leader joins BJP, says only PM Modi can save country |url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/tmc-leader-joins-bjp-says-222500604.html |accessdate=10 September 2019 |work=in.news.yahoo.com |date=1 March 2019 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=ANI |title=TMC leader joins BJP, says only PM Modi can save country |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/tmc-leader-joins-bjp-says-only-pm-modi-can-save-country/videoshow/68215587.cms?from=mdr |accessdate=12 February 2020 |date=1 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPramanik was born on 17 January 1986 to Bidhu Bhushan Pramanik and Chhanda Pramanik in [[Dinhata]] in [[Cooch behar district]] of [[West Bengal]]. He attained Bachelors of Computer Applications (B.C.A.) from Educated at Balakura Junior Basic School. He is married to Priyanka Pramanik, with whom he has two sons.<ref>{{cite web |title=Members : Lok Sabha |url=http://loksabhaph.nic.in/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=5041&lastls=17 |website=loksabhaph.nic.in |accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n*[http://loksabhaph.nic.in/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=5041&lastls=17 Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n\n{{17th Lok Sabha members from all states}}\n